###6. `configs/label_mapping.yaml`

```bashcat > configs/label_mapping.yaml <<'EOF'
mapped_aigc_label:
 human:
 description: Human-written or real human-generated content.
 aliases: ["human", "real_text", "organic"]
 ai_generated:
 description: AI-generated synthetic text or media.
 aliases: ["ai", "chatgpt", "synthetic", "generated"]
 real:
 description: Real image, video, or audio sample.
 aliases: ["real", "authentic"]
 fake:
 description: Manipulated or deepfake image, video, or audio sample.
 aliases: ["fake", "deepfake", "manipulated"]
 unknown:
 description: Label is unavailable or not verified.
 aliases: ["unknown", "unverified", "n/a"]

risk_type:
 normal:
 description: No obvious safety risk.
 sensitive:
 description: Sensitive but not directly public.
 violent:
 description: Violent or bloody content.
 sexual:
 description: Sexual or pornographic content.
 political:
 description: Political sensitive content.
 fraud:
 description: Fraud, scam, impersonation or misleading content.
 unknown:
 description: Risk type is unavailable or not verified.
EOF```

---

###7. `configs/quality_rules.yaml`

```bashcat > configs/quality_rules.yaml <<'EOF'
processing_status_rules:
 kept:
 description: Sample passes basic format, license and quality checks and can enter candidate pool.
 isolated_license:
 description: Dataset or sample has restricted or unclear redistribution permission. Raw data is isolated and not uploaded.
 metadata_only:
 description: Raw media is not stored in the repository. Only metadata and statistical records are retained.
 pending_review:
 description: Sample requires manual review before inclusion.
 rejected:
 description: Sample fails critical quality or governance checks and is excluded from the current candidate pool.

quality_checks:
 required_fields:
 - sample_id - dataset_name - modality - mapped_aigc_label - risk_type - processing_status duplicate_check:
 enabled: true key: file_hash license_check:
 enabled: true restricted_action: isolated_license sensitive_media_check:
 enabled: true action: metadata_only extreme_risk_content:
 action: isolated_metadata_retention description: Extreme risk samples are isolated. Metadata and risk labels are retained in controlled environment.
EOF```

